skip-link:
Here is an example of a skip link navigation that is focusable and at the top right after the opening body tag:

HTML:

```
<body>
  <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
  <header>
    <!-- header content here -->
  </header>
  <main id="main-content">
    <!-- main content here -->
  </main>
  <footer>
    <!-- footer content here -->
  </footer>
</body>
```

CSS:

```
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  left: 0;
  background-color: #fff;
  color: #000;
  padding: 10px;
  z-index: 999;
}

.skip-link:focus {
  top: 0;
}
```

In this example, the skip link navigation is an anchor tag with a class of "skip-link" and a href attribute that points to the ID of the main content section. The CSS positions the skip link at the top of the page and offscreen until it receives focus, at which point it moves into view. This allows keyboard users to easily skip over the header and navigation and go straight to the main content of the page.
